---
import BrandPageTemplate from '@/components/BrandPageTemplate.astro';
import CalibratedQuestionCTA from '@/components/CalibratedQuestionCTA.astro';
import FAQ from '@/components/FAQ.astro';
import { brand } from '@/data/brand';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How fast can you close on my house?',
    answer: "We can close in as few as 7 days from the time you accept our offer. Most sellers in the Kansas City area choose to close within 14-30 days, but we can work with any timeline up to 60 days. Because we pay cash, there's no bank approval process, no appraisal wait, and no financing contingencies that could cause delays. The title company needs about 3-5 business days for the title search and document preparation, and we can close as soon as that's complete. You pick the exact date.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need to make any repairs before selling?',
    answer: "No. We buy houses in any condition across the Kansas City metro. Foundation cracks, fire damage, mold, water damage, code violations, roof leaks, outdated kitchens and bathrooms, overgrown yards. None of it matters. We've purchased homes with collapsed ceilings, standing water in the basement, and active mold throughout. We've bought hoarder houses, condemned properties, and homes with every system failing. You don't need to fix, clean, paint, or renovate a single thing. Leave the house exactly as it is.",
  },
  {
    question: 'How do you determine your cash offer?',
    answer: "We start with the After Repair Value (ARV), which is what your home would sell for on the open market in perfect condition. We determine this by analyzing recent comparable sales in your specific neighborhood, accounting for square footage, lot size, number of bedrooms and bathrooms, and local market trends. Then we subtract our estimated repair costs (we itemize these so you can see each line item), our projected holding costs (taxes, insurance, utilities while we renovate), our selling costs when we resell, and our profit margin. We share the full breakdown with you so the offer is completely transparent. If you disagree with any of our estimates, we're happy to discuss.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Are there any fees or commissions?',
    answer: "Zero. There are no agent commissions (because no agents are involved), no closing costs (we pay them all), no processing fees, no administrative fees, and no hidden charges. The number on our cash offer is the amount you walk away with at closing, minus only your existing mortgage payoff and any liens on the title. We don't deduct anything from the offer amount. If we say $120,000, you get $120,000 before your own debts.",
  },
  {
    question: 'What types of properties do you buy?',
    answer: "We buy single-family homes, duplexes, triplexes, and small multi-family properties (up to 4 units) across the Kansas City metro area. We purchase in Jackson County, Clay County, and Platte County in Missouri, plus Wyandotte County and Johnson County in Kansas. We buy in every neighborhood from downtown KC to the suburbs. We buy homes in any condition, any price range, and any situation: occupied, vacant, tenant-occupied, estate properties, properties with liens, properties with code violations, even condemned properties.",
  },
  {
    question: 'What if my house is in pre-foreclosure?',
    answer: "We work with homeowners in pre-foreclosure regularly across the KC metro. A cash sale can stop the foreclosure process, protect your credit score, and put cash in your pocket. The key is timing. Once you get a notice of default, you typically have 20-30 days before the foreclosure moves to the next stage. We can close within that window. Even if you're further along in the process, we may still be able to help. The sooner you call, the more options you have. We've helped homeowners in Jackson County, Clay County, and Wyandotte County stop foreclosure by closing fast enough to pay off the mortgage and put the remaining equity in their pocket.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I have to accept your offer?',
    answer: "Absolutely not. Our cash offer is completely no-obligation. We present it, explain how we got to the number, and give you time to think about it. There's no expiration pressure and no hard feelings if you decide to go another route. We encourage you to get a listing agent's opinion as well and compare the two side by side. If listing makes more sense for your situation, do that. We want you to make the best decision for your family, even if that means not selling to us.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I sell if I still owe money on the mortgage?',
    answer: 'Yes. The majority of homeowners we work with still have a mortgage balance. At closing, the title company pays off your remaining mortgage directly from the sale proceeds. You receive whatever is left after the payoff. If you owe more on the mortgage than the home is worth (known as being "underwater"), we can discuss short sale options with your lender. In a short sale, the lender agrees to accept less than the full mortgage balance. We have experience negotiating short sales with most major mortgage servicers.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How is this different from listing with an agent?',
    answer: "The main differences are speed, cost, and certainty. Listing with an agent in Kansas City typically takes 3-6 months from listing to closing. You'll pay 5-6% in agent commissions ($7,500-$18,000 on a typical KC home), 1-3% in closing costs, and $5,000-$30,000+ in repairs to make the home \"show ready.\" You'll host multiple showings with strangers walking through your house. And roughly 15-20% of MLS deals fall through when the buyer's financing doesn't come through. Selling to us takes days, not months. There are zero repairs, zero commissions, zero closing costs, and one short walkthrough. We pay cash, so there's no financing risk. The tradeoff is that our offer is below full retail value, since we're taking on all the risk and repair costs. For homes that need work or for homeowners who need speed and certainty, the math often favors the cash route.",
  },
  {
    question: 'What happens after I accept the offer?',
    answer: "We open escrow with a local Kansas City title company (we use established title companies in the KC metro that specialize in real estate closings). The title company runs a title search to identify any liens, encumbrances, or ownership issues. This takes 3-5 business days. If issues are found, we work with the title company to resolve them at closing. A few days before your chosen closing date, the title company sends you the settlement statement showing all the numbers: sale price, mortgage payoff (if any), lien payoffs (if any), and your net proceeds. On closing day, you sign the deed and closing documents at the title company's office. Your funds are released the same day via wire transfer to your bank account or by cashier's check.",
  },
  {
    question: 'What if my house has a lien or judgment against it?',
    answer: "Liens and judgments don't prevent a cash sale. The title company identifies all liens during the title search and resolves them at closing from the sale proceeds. Common liens include property tax liens, mechanic's liens (from unpaid contractors), HOA liens, and court judgments. In some cases, we can negotiate with lien holders to accept less than the full amount owed. If the total liens exceed the property value, we can discuss options including short sale negotiations.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you buy houses with tenants still living in them?',
    answer: "Yes. We buy tenant-occupied properties regularly. Whether your tenant is current on rent, behind on rent, or refusing to leave, we can still purchase the property. We take over the landlord responsibilities at closing and handle the tenant situation from there. You don't need to evict your tenant before selling. This is one of the most common reasons Kansas City landlords sell to us.",
  },
  {
    question: 'What areas of Kansas City do you serve?',
    answer: "We buy homes across the entire Kansas City metro area covering 5 counties: Jackson County (Kansas City, Independence, Blue Springs, Lee's Summit, Raytown, Grandview), Clay County (Liberty, Gladstone, Excelsior Springs, Kearney, Smithville, North Kansas City), Platte County (Parkville, Platte City, Weston, Riverside), Wyandotte County (Kansas City KS, Bonner Springs, Edwardsville), and Johnson County (Overland Park, Olathe, Shawnee, Lenexa, Merriam). If your property is in the KC metro area, we can probably buy it.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Is Saving KC Homebuyers a legitimate company?',
    answer: `${brand.name} is a registered business operating out of ${brand.address.full}. ${brand.ownerName} is the owner and operator. We've been buying homes in the Kansas City metro since ${brand.foundedYear}. You can visit our office, call us directly at ${brand.phoneFormatted}, and verify our business registration. Every transaction closes through a licensed Kansas City title company, which provides an independent third party to handle the funds and legal documents.`,
  },
];

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faqs.map(f => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: f.question,
    acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: f.answer },
  })),
};
---

<BrandPageTemplate
  title="FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions About Selling Your House for Cash"
  description={`Get answers to common questions about selling your Kansas City home for cash to ${brand.name}. Learn about our process, timeline, offers, and what to expect.`}
  canonical={`${brand.domain}/faq/`}
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'FAQ' }]}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <h1 class="page-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">
    Common questions from Kansas City homeowners about selling their house for cash. If you don't see your question here, call us at {brand.phoneFormatted} and we'll answer it directly.
  </p>

  <FAQ items={faqs} />

  <!-- Additional context -->
  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        Every homeowner's situation is different. The questions above cover the most common concerns we hear, but your specific circumstances might raise questions we haven't addressed here. That's why we encourage you to call us directly at {brand.phoneFormatted} or fill out the form on our contact page.
      </p>
      <p>
        The initial conversation takes about 5 minutes and costs you nothing. We'll answer every question you have, explain exactly how the process works for your specific situation, and give you a preliminary idea of what your property might be worth in a cash sale. No pressure, no obligation, no sales pitch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CalibratedQuestionCTA />
</BrandPageTemplate>

<style>
  .page-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .page-desc {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--grey-500);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--grey-100);
  }

  .section-body {
    color: var(--grey-700);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .section-body p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .section-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .page-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
